AmaZulu Prime Minister, Mangosuthu Buthelezi addresses the nation #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 Editor's Note: The Livestream has already, however you may watch the recording above KWANONGOMA - AmaZulu Prime Minister, Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi, addressed the media on Saturday. This after Prince Misuzulu was named the preferred King in his mother's will. READ: IFP welcomes Prince Misuzulu's nomination as next AmaZulu King Queen Regent, Mantfombi Dlamini-Zulu's will was read Friday night, prompting a flurry of activity at the KwaKhangelamankengane Royal Palace. The prince was driven away by armed guards. He is now in meetings with Buthelezi at the palace in KwaNongoma.